roughdreamz WhatsApp Bot - Plan
=================================

PURPOSE
-------
Baileys-based WhatsApp bot that reads schedule messages from WhatsApp groups,
parses them (AI + regex fallback), and auto-upserts them into the Supabase
`schedules` table — replacing the manual copy-paste workflow.

HOW IT WORKS
------------
1. Connect via WhatsApp Web protocol using Baileys library
2. Listens for new messages in groups (@g.us)
3. On receiving a text message, runs AI parsing (Gemini → OpenRouter)
4. If AI fails, falls back to regex-based Swahili schedule parser
5. Upserts parsed schedule into Supabase `schedules` table
6. Replies to the group with a confirmation in Swahili
7. Auth persists via auth_info/ folder (QR scan once)

Unlike the Meta Cloud API webhook (which requires a public HTTPS endpoint),
this bot connects directly via WhatsApp Web — no hosting needed.

FILES
-----
index.js                   - Main bot entry point
package.json               - Dependencies & scripts
.env                       - Environment variables (keys, URLs)
plan                       - This file
src/
├── parseScheduleMessage.js - Regex-based Swahili ferry schedule parser
├── parseWithAI.js          - AI parser (Gemini → OpenRouter fallback)
└── supabaseAdmin.js        - Supabase admin client (bypasses RLS)

ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (.env)
----------------------------
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL   - Supabase project URL
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY  - Supabase service role key (bypasses RLS)
GEMINI_API_KEY             - Google Gemini API key
OPENROUTER_API_KEY         - OpenRouter API key (fallback AI)

Optional:
TARGET_GROUP_JID           - Only process messages from this group JID
LOG_LEVEL                  - Pino log level (default: info)

RUNNING
-------
npm start       # normal
npm run dev     # with --watch (auto-restart on file changes)

On first run, a QR code will print in the terminal.
Scan it with WhatsApp (Linked Devices) to authenticate.
The session persists in auth_info/ folder.

SCHEDULES TABLE (Supabase)
--------------------------
ship_name  - e.g. "MV Kilindoni"
route      - e.g. "Mafia Island - Nyamisati"
days       - e.g. "Monday" (English)
date       - YYYY-MM-DD
departure  - HH:MM (24hr)
arrival    - HH:MM (24hr)
duration   - e.g. "5 hours"
notes      - weather disclaimers or extra info

KEY DIFFERENCES FROM WEBHOOK
----------------------------
Webhook (Meta API)              | Baileys Bot
--------------------------------|-------------------------------
Requires public HTTPS endpoint  | Runs locally, connects via WhatsApp Web
Triggered by Meta POST request  | Listens to messages in real-time
Uses WHATSAPP_TOKEN / PHONE_ID  | Uses QR scan authentication
Can only read messages          | Can read ALL group messages
Meta Cloud API (official)       | WhatsApp Web protocol (unofficial)
sendTextMessage via Graph API   | sock.sendMessage (direct)
